# TheToppers Documentation

## Objective

Gain access to the target web application, upload a web shell through exposed S3 storage, execute commands remotely, and retrieve the flag.

---

# Phase 1 — Configure AWS CLI

Initial AWS configuration:

```bash
aws configure
```

Entered values:

```text
AWS Access Key ID: test
AWS Secret Access Key: test
Default region name: test
Default output format: test
```

The first configuration attempt failed because credentials were missing.

Verification command:

```bash
aws --endpoint-url http://s3.thetoppers.htb s3 ls
```

Result:

```text
2026-05-13 16:24:08 thetoppers.htb
```

This confirmed:

* S3-compatible storage was exposed.
* Credentials were accepted.
* Bucket enumeration worked.

