# Final Result

Successfully:

* Enumerated exposed S3 storage
* Uploaded PHP web shell
* Achieved remote command execution
* Enumerated filesystem
* Located and read the flag


Conclusion

he objective of this assessment was to identify and exploit vulnerabilities present on the target system and obtain access to sensitive information. Initial reconnaissance revealed that the target was hosted on an Amazon AWS infrastructure and utilized an S3 bucket associated with the web application.

During enumeration, a misconfigured S3 bucket was discovered that permitted unauthorized write access. This critical misconfiguration allowed arbitrary file uploads to the web server environment. By leveraging this weakness, a PHP web shell was successfully uploaded and executed remotely, resulting in command execution on the target system.

Once command execution was established, post-exploitation enumeration was conducted to identify the execution context, available users, accessible directories, and potential locations of user and system flags. Enumeration revealed execution under a restricted service account (www-data) with limited permissions. Multiple attempts were made to locate standard user flag locations under /home and other common directories; however, the expected flag was not present in those locations.

